| **Hit Dice** | 7d8+21 (52 hp) |
| **Initiative** | +1 |
| **Speed** | 10 ft. (2 squares) |
| **Armor Class** | 15 (+1 Dex, +4 natural), touch 11, flat-footed 14 |
| **Base Attack/Grapple** | +5/+8 |
| **Attack** | Slam +9 melee (1d8+4) |
| **Full Attack** | 2 slams +9 melee (1d8+4) |
| **Space/Reach** | 5 ft./5 ft. |
| **Special Attacks** | Adhesive, crush |
| **Special Qualities** | Darkvision 60 ft., immunity to acid, mimic shape, elemental resonance (none — aberrant) |
| **Saves** | Fort +5, Ref +5, Will +6 |
| **Abilities** | Str 19, Dex 12, Con 17, Int 10, Wis 13, Cha 10 |
| **Skills** | Climb +9, Disguise +13 (includes +10 racial when mimicking objects), Listen +8, Spot +8 |
| **Feats** | Alertness, Lightning Reflexes, Weapon Focus (slam) |
| **Elemental Affinity** | None — mimics exist outside the elemental framework entirely; their physiology registers as an absence that is not Dómnathar void but simply *nothing* |
| **Environment** | Giant Ruins (the interior rooms, corridors, and vaults of Giant-era ruin-complexes throughout the Infinite Desert — any structure where there are objects to mimic and prey to attract; secondary populations in Vestri deep-mines and Dómnathar-adjacent tunnel-systems) |
| **Organization** | Solitary |
| **Challenge Rating** | 4 |
| **Treasure** | 1/10th coins; 50% goods; 50% items |
| **Alignment** | Usually neutral |
| **Advancement** | 8–10 HD (Medium); 11–14 HD (Large) |
| **Level Adjustment** | — |

### Combat

A mimic waits in its assumed shape until a creature touches it, then attacks with its adhesive-coated slam. Once a target is stuck, the mimic crushes. It does not pursue fleeing targets — it returns to object form and waits for the next victim.

### Special Abilities

**Adhesive (Ex):** A mimic exudes a thick, glue-like slime. Anything that touches the mimic is automatically stuck (Strength DC 16 to pull free, or DC 16 Escape Artist). Weapons that strike a mimic stick on a successful hit. Alcohol dissolves the adhesive (flask of alcohol applied as a full-round action releases one stuck item or limb).

**Crush (Ex):** A mimic deals 1d8+4 damage each round to any stuck creature as it folds around the victim.

**Mimic Shape (Ex):** A mimic can assume the shape of any Medium object (chest, door, table, bed, large crate). The disguise is nearly perfect (+10 racial bonus to Disguise when mimicking an object). Only a DC 25 Spot check reveals the deception before physical contact.

**Aberrant Non-Resonance (Su):** A mimic has no elemental resonance at all — not Dómnathar void-silence (which reads as deliberate absence) but simply no reading, as though the creature does not exist on the metaphysical plane. This is deeply unsettling to Kin who notice it — the sensation of looking at a solid object and feeling nothing where *something* should register, even as background. Detection of this non-resonance requires a Kin to actively scan (move action, DC 14 Wisdom check) — mimics do not trigger passive Kin-sense at all.

### Society

Mimics are solitary ambush predators of the ruin-interior — intelligent (Int 10), patient, and superbly adapted to their niche. They are most common in Giant ruins, where the abundance of Giant-sized furniture and objects provides an enormous range of shapes to assume, and the steady trickle of ruin-explorers provides prey.

Pekakarlik ruin-expeditions drill anti-mimic protocols alongside anti-medusa protocols. The Pekakarlik approach: probe every object with a ten-foot pole before touching it. This is unglamorous, time-consuming, and effective. Pekakarlik veterans carry flasks of alcohol specifically for mimic-adhesive dissolution.

### Lore

**DC 14 (Knowledge [dungeoneering]):** Mimics are shapeshifting aberrations that assume the form of objects and attack when touched. Their adhesive traps anything that contacts them. Alcohol dissolves the glue.

**DC 19:** Mimics are intelligent (Int 10) and can be negotiated with — some will trade information about a ruin’s layout in exchange for food. They are immune to acid. A ten-foot pole is the standard counter-measure.

**DC 24:** Mimics have no elemental resonance — they are metaphysically invisible to passive Kin-sense, a property unique among Oreka’s non-Dómnathar creatures. This suggests an origin entirely outside the elemental framework — possibly a Giant-era experiment or an extraplanar immigrant.

# MINOTAUR

The labyrinth was not built for you. It was built for something larger, something that moves through these corridors with the confidence of a creature that has memorised every turn. You have been lost for two hours. You hear it breathe — a deep, slow rasp of something big drawing air through a bovine muzzle — and then the sound of hooves on stone, accelerating.

**Large Monstrous Humanoid**

